<item>
            <title>[NIFI-8365] JSON record reader mishandles deep CHOICE types</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/NIFI-8365</link>
                <project id="12316020" key="NIFI">Apache NiFi</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The AbstractJsonRowRecordReader when trying to find the correct schema for a given record it may come with a wrong one.&lt;br/&gt;
For example:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suppose the following record:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-json&quot;&gt;
{
  &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;dataCollection&quot;&lt;/span&gt;:[
    {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;record&quot;&lt;/span&gt;: {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;integer&quot;&lt;/span&gt;: 1,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;boolean&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&quot;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;true&lt;/span&gt;
      }
    },
    {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;record&quot;&lt;/span&gt;: {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;integer&quot;&lt;/span&gt;: 2,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;string&quot;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;stringValue2&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
      }
    }
  ]
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Even if the schema is correctly set (which may not be the case as infer schema itself has a similar issue),&lt;br/&gt;
the second record&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-json&quot;&gt;
    {
      &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;record&quot;&lt;/span&gt;: {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;integer&quot;&lt;/span&gt;: 2,
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;string&quot;&lt;/span&gt;: &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;stringValue2&quot;&lt;/span&gt;
      }
    }
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;p&gt;will be assigned the schema of the first (&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot;integer&amp;quot; : &amp;quot;INT&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;boolean&amp;quot; : &amp;quot;BOOLEAN&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; instead of &lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;&amp;quot;integer&amp;quot; : &amp;quot;INT&amp;quot;, &amp;quot;string&amp;quot; : &amp;quot;STRING&amp;quot;&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will cause the fields that are not present in the schema (in this case &quot;string&quot;) to be omitted when writing it out.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
